<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="180" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,682,1211]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,682,707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(refined after 
<bibRefCitation box="[437,565,682,707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180" refId="ref7997" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article">Cook 1974</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[627,861,682,707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180" refId="ref8025" refString="Gerecke, R., Gledhill, T., Pesiae, V. &amp; Smit, H. (2016) 8. Acari: Hydrachnidia III. In: Gerecke, R. (Ed.), Suβwasserfauna von Mitteleuropa. 7 / 2 - 3. Elsevier GmbH, Akademischer Verlag, Berlin / Heidelberg, pp. 1 - 429." type="journal article">
Gerecke 
<emphasis box="[730,790,683,707]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Dorsal and ventral shield present. Dorsal shield elongated, without modifications, no cauda development, bearing five pairs of setae (
<emphasis box="[1106,1295,719,742]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Oi, Oe, Hi, Li, Si</emphasis>
), trichothria 
<emphasis box="[151,226,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Fp, Oi</emphasis>
and setae 
<emphasis box="[351,376,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Pi</emphasis>
always not associated with glandularia; in addition, setae 
<emphasis box="[1049,1114,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Si, Ci</emphasis>
may be not associated with glandularia, other idiosomal setae associated with glandularia. Setae 
<emphasis box="[931,1199,790,814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Fch, Fp, Vi, He, Sci, Le</emphasis>
and five pairs of slit organs (
<emphasis box="[242,302,827,851]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">
<date box="[242,302,827,851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">i1- i5</date>
</emphasis>
) in the membranous dorsal furrow, first pair of slit organs touching or fused with the sclerite bearing seta and glandularium 
<emphasis box="[409,432,863,886]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Vi</emphasis>
on each side. Excretory pore free or fused to dorsal shield. Tips of anterior coxal plates reaching or extending beyond anterior idiosoma margin. Ventral shield bearing setae 
<emphasis box="[1109,1286,899,922]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Hv, Ve, Sce, Pe.</emphasis>
Setae 
<emphasis box="[1361,1388,899,922]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Ci</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,176,935,958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Pi</emphasis>
located on small transversal sclerites caudally. Coxal plates IV with two pairs of muscle attachment scars: posteriomedial and posteriolateral or posteriomedial muscle attachment scars not developed. Genital field with three pairs of acetabula. Legs without swimming setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[791,851,1006,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Male</emphasis>
: Аcetabular plates fused to form an unpaired plate bearing a few genital setae, surrounding the gonopore; this plate may be free in the soft integument or fused with the posterior margin of ventral shield, setae and glandularia 
<emphasis box="[839,865,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Se</emphasis>
free or fused with ventral shield posteriolaterally. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,238,1114,1139]" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Female</emphasis>
: Аcetabular plates separated, expanded anteriorly and narrowed posteriorly, setae and glandularia 
<emphasis box="[1357,1383,1115,1138]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="180">Se</emphasis>
free either fused with ventral shield or fused with acetabular plates; postgenital sclerite free, fused with dorsal shield or with acetabular plates.
</paragraph>
